{"article_id":"eUnDOBrJDY4Q0emZ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A single student ' s case has turned into a massive legal decision for all transgender Americans .","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"On Tuesday , the Seventh Circuit Court of Appeals ruled","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"that the Kenosha Unified School District in Wisconsin violated the rights of a trans student , Ash Whitaker ,","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"when it refused to let him use the boys ' bathroom .","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"According to the court ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"Whitaker is likely to win upon a full review of the case","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"( instead of the current review of a lower court ' s preliminary injunction )","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"on his claim","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"that the school ' s actions violated Title IX , a federal law","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"that prohibits discrimination in schools","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"based on sex ,","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"and the Equal Protections Clause of the 14th Amendment .","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"So it upheld a lower court ' s injunction","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"forcing the school to let Whitaker use the bathroom","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"that aligns with his gender identity .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"In the decision , a three-judge panel from the Seventh Circuit Court concluded","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"that the school district \" has failed to provide any evidence","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"of how the preliminary injunction will harm it , or any of its students or parents \"","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"- a rebuke of the prevalent myth","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"that letting trans people use the bathroom for their gender identity will hurt others .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"The ruling has big implications :","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"If existing federal law and the 14th Amendment shield trans people from discrimination ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"then it ' s not just Whitaker ' s rights that are protected here ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"but all trans students ' .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"And","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"if bans against sex discrimination in particular apply to trans people ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"then it ' s not just students ' rights that are protected ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"but all trans people","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"who face discrimination in other settings","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"where sex discrimination is banned","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"- so not just schools , but the workplace and housing as well .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"\" This powerful decision","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"- another in a growing list of rulings","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"affirming the constitutional rights of transgender people -","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"helps Ash and tens of thousands of students like him get the same opportunity","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"to learn as any other student , \"","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"National Center for Transgender Equality executive director Mara Keisling said in a statement .","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"\" It recognizes","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"that fully respecting and including transgender students like Ash Whitaker is legally and morally the right thing","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"to do ,","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"and that discrimination against these young people","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"because of who they are","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"is cruel , wrong and illegal . \"","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"The ruling comes on the heels of similar court battles , particularly that of Gavin Grimm in Virginia .","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"That case briefly rose to the US Supreme Court ,","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"which","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"LGBTQ advocates hoped","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"would decide the legal issue","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"- of whether Title IX really applies to trans people .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"since the Trump administration rescinded a legal guidance","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"protecting trans people","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"that was attached to Grimm ' s situation ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"the court punted on the case ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"sending it back down to the lower courts .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"The Seventh Circuit Court ' s case does not have the limitation","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"of being attached to the guidance or any other regulation","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"that the Trump administration could rescind .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Instead , it poses the straight question :","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"Are trans people protected under federal law ?","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"If other courts agree with the Seventh Circuit Court ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"that could reshape the face of civil rights laws in America","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"- and help fill a void","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"that ' s left trans people legally unprotected from discrimination across most of the US .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"Under most states ' laws and federal law , trans people aren ' t explicitly protected from discrimination in the workplace , housing , public accommodations , and schools .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"This means that a person can be fired from a job ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"evicted from a home ,","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"kicked out of a business ,","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"or denied the correct bathroom facility","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"just because an employer , landlord , business owner , or school principal doesn ' t approve of the person ' s gender identity .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"LGBTQ advocates argue , however ,","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"that federal civil rights law should already shield trans people from discrimination .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"The argument :","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"Discrimination against someone","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"based on their gender identity","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"is fundamentally rooted in sex-based expectations .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"For example ,","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"if someone discriminates against a trans woman ,","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"that ' s largely based on the expectation","depth":15},{"id":79,"text":"that a person","depth":17},{"id":80,"text":"designated male at birth","depth":17},{"id":81,"text":"should identify as a man -","depth":16},{"id":82,"text":"a belief","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"built on an idea","depth":17},{"id":84,"text":"of what a person of a certain sex","depth":18},{"id":85,"text":"assigned at birth","depth":18},{"id":86,"text":"should be like .","depth":16},{"id":87,"text":"So","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"since federal civil rights laws , such as Title IX , ban sex discrimination in the workplace , housing , and schools ,","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"they should ban discrimination against trans people in these settings as well .","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"This isn ' t just a wild interpretation by LGBTQ advocates ;","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"there ' s legal precedent for it .","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"Joshua Block , an American Civil Liberties Union attorney","depth":16},{"id":93,"text":"who worked on Grimm ' s case ,","depth":16},{"id":94,"text":"cited a 1998 Supreme Court case , Oncale v. Sundowner Offshore Services Inc. ,","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"in which the Court unanimously agreed","depth":16},{"id":96,"text":"that bans on sex discrimination prohibit same-sex sexual harassment .","depth":16},{"id":97,"text":"Same-sex sexual harassment was not something","depth":17},{"id":98,"text":"the authors of federal civil rights laws considered ,","depth":17},{"id":99,"text":"but it ' s something ,","depth":18},{"id":100,"text":"the Supreme Court said ,","depth":18},{"id":101,"text":"that a plain reading of the law protects .","depth":17},{"id":102,"text":"\" Oncale says","depth":17},{"id":103,"text":"that ' s irrelevant whether [ Congress ] contemplated it , \"","depth":17},{"id":104,"text":"Block previously told me .","depth":16},{"id":105,"text":"\" That ' s not how laws work .","depth":16},{"id":106,"text":"This is literal sex discrimination .","depth":16},{"id":107,"text":"Whether or not that ' s what Congress was focused on doesn ' t make it any less a type of discrimination","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"covered by the statute . \"","depth":15},{"id":109,"text":"Seventh Circuit Judge Ann Claire Williams embraced this view in her ruling on Tuesday :","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"\" A policy","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"that requires an individual to use a bathroom","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"that does not conform with his or her gender identity","depth":15},{"id":113,"text":"punishes that individual for his or her gender non‐conformance ,","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"which in turn violates Title IX . \"","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"But the court went even further","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"- arguing","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"that the Kenosha Unified School District ' s actions violated the 14th Amendment .","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"The school district claimed","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"that it treats all boys and girls equally -","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"meaning it forces them all to use certain bathrooms","depth":15},{"id":121,"text":"based on the sex","depth":17},{"id":122,"text":"they were assigned at birth","depth":17},{"id":123,"text":"instead of their gender identity .","depth":16},{"id":124,"text":"But Williams ruled","depth":15},{"id":125,"text":"that this is \" untrue , \"","depth":15},{"id":126,"text":"adding ,","depth":15},{"id":127,"text":"\" Rather , the School District treats transgender students like Ash ,","depth":17},{"id":128,"text":"who fail to conform to the sex‐based stereotypes","depth":18},{"id":129,"text":"associated with their assigned sex at birth ,","depth":18},{"id":130,"text":"differently . \"","depth":16},{"id":131,"text":"Anti-trans bathroom policies harm trans people","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"- and are based on a myth","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"Anti-trans policies like the Kenosha Unified School District ' s do real harm to trans students .","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"Forcing trans people to use the bathroom","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"that doesn ' t align with their gender identity","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"acts as a reminder","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"as far as society has come on some LGBTQ issues ,","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"it ' s still not completely willing to accept trans people and their identities","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"- even if trans people pose no danger to anyone else .","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"Indeed , this is exactly the argument","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"that the Seventh Circuit Court seemingly sided with .","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"The court ' s ruling stated :","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"[ Whitaker ] asserted","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"that the denial of access to the boys ' bathroom was causing him harm ,","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"as his attempts","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"to avoid using the bathroom","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"exacerbated his vasovagal syncope , a condition","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"that renders Ash susceptible to fainting and/or seizures","depth":15},{"id":150,"text":"if dehydrated .","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"He also contended","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"that the denial caused him educational and emotional harm ,","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"including suicidal ideations .","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"Under anti-trans measures , trans people have to constantly fear using the bathroom","depth":8},{"id":155,"text":"that corresponds with their gender identity .","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"As Lily Carollo wrote for ,","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"\" From now until the law is repealed or settled in court ,","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"or until my birth certificate is amended ,","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"I will keep breaking the law .","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"I ' m not the only one .","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"I will be an anxious mess","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"every time I use the bathroom ,","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"but I don ' t see any option .","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"It ' s all","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"I can do , really .","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"I am a woman . \"","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"Grimm , a teenage trans activist","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"who sued his school for bathroom access ,","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"framed it another way .","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"\" This wasn ' t just about bathrooms .","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"It was about the right","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"to exist in public spaces for trans people , \"","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"Grimm previously told me ,","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"quoting trans actress Laverne Cox .","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"\" Without the access to appropriate bathrooms ,","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"there ' s so much","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"that you ' re limited in doing .","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"If you try to imagine what your day would be like","depth":12},{"id":179,"text":"if you had absolutely no restrooms","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"to use","depth":14},{"id":181,"text":"other than the home ,","depth":14},{"id":182,"text":"it would take planning .","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"You would probably find yourself avoiding liquids ,","depth":11},{"id":184,"text":"probably avoiding eating ,","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"maybe going out in public for too long at a time . \"","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"At the same time , a major argument","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"used","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"to impose anti-trans policies","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"is based on a total myth :","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"that letting trans people use the bathroom or locker room for their gender identity will allow men to disguise themselves as trans women","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"to go into women ' s bathrooms or locker rooms","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"and sexually assault and harass women .","depth":13},{"id":193,"text":"But","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"even if trans people are allowed to use the bathroom or locker room","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"that aligns with their gender identity ,","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"sexual assault remains illegal .","depth":12},{"id":197,"text":"There ' s also no evidence","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"that nondiscrimination laws","depth":13},{"id":199,"text":"- and other policies","depth":14},{"id":200,"text":"that let trans people use the bathroom for their gender identity -","depth":14},{"id":201,"text":"lead to sexual assault in bathrooms and locker rooms .","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"In two investigations , the left-leaning media watchdog organization Media Matters confirmed with experts and officials in 12 states and 17 school districts with protections for trans people","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"that they had no increases in sex crimes","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"after they enacted their policies .","depth":12},{"id":205,"text":"Conservatives","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"who favor these policies","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"usually counter","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"that there are examples of men","depth":11},{"id":209,"text":"sneaking into women ' s bathrooms","depth":12},{"id":210,"text":"to attack women .","depth":12},{"id":211,"text":"But","depth":12},{"id":212,"text":"as PolitiFact reported ,","depth":13},{"id":213,"text":"none of the examples","depth":15},{"id":214,"text":"cited in the US","depth":15},{"id":215,"text":"happened after a city or state passed a nondiscrimination law","depth":15},{"id":216,"text":"or otherwise let trans people use the bathroom or locker room for their gender identity .","depth":15},{"id":217,"text":"Instead , these seem to be examples of men","depth":13},{"id":218,"text":"doing awful things","depth":14},{"id":219,"text":"regardless of the law","depth":14},{"id":220,"text":"- which has , unfortunately , happened since the beginning of civilization .","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"One example is a case in Toronto , Canada ,","depth":13},{"id":222,"text":"which now has a nondiscrimination law ,","depth":13},{"id":223,"text":"in which a man disguised himself as a woman","depth":13},{"id":224,"text":"and attacked women in shelters .","depth":13},{"id":225,"text":"But the attacks happened months before Ontario","depth":14},{"id":226,"text":"( Toronto ' s province )","depth":14},{"id":227,"text":"protected trans people in a nondiscrimination law .","depth":13},{"id":228,"text":"So the law couldn ' t have been the cause .","depth":12},{"id":229,"text":"While the issue is now being used primarily against trans people ,","depth":10},{"id":230,"text":"historically bathroom fears have been regularly deployed against civil rights causes .","depth":10},{"id":231,"text":"They were used against black people","depth":12},{"id":232,"text":"to justify segregation -","depth":13},{"id":233,"text":"by invoking fears","depth":14},{"id":234,"text":"that black men would attack white women in bathrooms .","depth":14},{"id":235,"text":"And they were used","depth":12},{"id":236,"text":"to stop the Equal Rights Amendment ,","depth":14},{"id":237,"text":"which tried to establish legal equality between men and women ,","depth":14},{"id":238,"text":"because opponents claimed","depth":14},{"id":239,"text":"it would lead to the abolition of bathrooms for different genders ,","depth":15},{"id":240,"text":"potentially putting women in danger .","depth":15},{"id":241,"text":"Some people are also , frankly , just bothered by the idea","depth":11},{"id":242,"text":"that someone in the same bathroom or locker room won ' t share the same genitalia as them .","depth":11},{"id":243,"text":"This gets to the heart of the issue :","depth":12},{"id":244,"text":"Bathrooms are places","depth":14},{"id":245,"text":"where really private things happen ,","depth":14},{"id":246,"text":"and that makes people feel vulnerable in all sorts of ways .","depth":13},{"id":247,"text":"\" People are afraid","depth":13},{"id":248,"text":"because they ' re exposed , \"","depth":13},{"id":249,"text":"Kathryn Anthony , author of Designing for Diversity : Gender , Race and Ethnicity in the Architectural Profession ,","depth":13},{"id":250,"text":"told the Guardian .","depth":13},{"id":251,"text":"\" There ' s a vulnerability","depth":11},{"id":252,"text":"we feel in public restrooms","depth":12},{"id":253,"text":"we don ' t feel in other places . \"","depth":12},{"id":254,"text":"But a lot of things happen in public bathrooms","depth":12},{"id":255,"text":"that people aren ' t comfortable with -","depth":12},{"id":256,"text":"and people have managed to deal with it","depth":12},{"id":257,"text":"to accommodate others ' rights and needs .","depth":12},{"id":258,"text":"So","depth":12},{"id":259,"text":"if it ' s not harming anyone ,","depth":14},{"id":260,"text":"perhaps it ' s best ,","depth":15},{"id":261,"text":"LGBTQ advocates argue ,","depth":15},{"id":262,"text":"to let trans people use the facility for their gender identity","depth":14},{"id":263,"text":"without making them feel ostracized and discriminated against .","depth":14},{"id":264,"text":"( Discrimination is a huge contributor to gender dysphoria , a medical condition","depth":13},{"id":265,"text":"some trans people experience","depth":13},{"id":266,"text":"that can cause depression , anxiety , and even suicidal ideation . )","depth":12},{"id":267,"text":"On Tuesday , the Seventh Circuit Court sided with this view .","depth":2},{"id":268,"text":"It agreed","depth":4},{"id":269,"text":"that there is no evidence","depth":5},{"id":270,"text":"that letting Whitaker use the bathroom for his gender identity will cause any harm to anyone else ,","depth":5},{"id":271,"text":"while acknowledging the clear harms","depth":4},{"id":272,"text":"the school ' s policy had done to him .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":545,"left":539,"right":544,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":539,"left":315,"right":538,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":315,"left":303,"right":314,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":303,"left":292,"right":302,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":292,"left":287,"right":291,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":287,"left":276,"right":286,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":0,"right":275,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":275,"left":1,"right":274,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":274,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":286,"left":283,"right":285,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":4,"right":282,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":282,"left":278,"right":281,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":278,"left":277,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":277,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":281,"left":280,"right":11,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":280,"left":8,"right":279,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":279,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":12,"right":284,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":284,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":291,"left":289,"right":290,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":289,"left":15,"right":288,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":288,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":290,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":20,"right":301,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":301,"left":294,"right":300,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":294,"left":21,"right":293,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":293,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":300,"left":24,"right":299,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":299,"left":25,"right":298,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":298,"left":26,"right":297,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":297,"left":296,"right":30,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":27,"right":295,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":28,"right":29,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":314,"left":307,"right":313,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":307,"left":305,"right":306,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":305,"left":31,"right":304,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":304,"left":32,"right":33,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":34,"right":35,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":313,"left":36,"right":312,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":312,"left":37,"right":311,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":311,"left":308,"right":310,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":308,"left":38,"right":39,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":310,"left":309,"right":42,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":309,"left":40,"right":41,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":538,"left":402,"right":537,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":402,"left":326,"right":401,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":326,"left":43,"right":325,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":325,"left":319,"right":324,"relation":"adversativ